"High dietary fat intake","Regular breast self-examination","Smoking"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESmoking\u003C/strong\u003E is a significant risk factor for non-lactational mastitis. It causes damage to the ductal epithelium and promotes periductal inflammation, leading to ductal ectasia and subsequent infection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERegular breast self-examination\u003C/strong\u003E is a preventive measure and does not increase mastitis risk\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHigh dietary fat intake\u003C/strong\u003E has not been shown to influence mastitis development\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERegular exercise\u003C/strong\u003E is generally protective for breast health and does not increase infection risk\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOral contraceptive use\u003C/strong\u003E has no established connection to non-lactational mastitis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther important risk factors for non-lactational mastitis include diabetes mellitus, nipple inversion or piercing, obesity, and underlying breast conditions such as ductal ectasia. The condition is most common in perimenopausal women.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Non-lactational mastitis commonly occurs in perimenopausal women due to ductal ectasia and inflammation.","Risk factors for non-lactational mastitis include smoking, diabetes mellitus, and nipple inversion or piercing."],"references":["Zeng Y, Zhang D, Fu N, Zhao W, Huang Q, Cui J, Chen Y, Liu Z, Zhang X, Zhang S, Mansoor KM. Risk Factors for Granulomatous Mastitis and Establishment and Validation of a Clinical Prediction Model (Nomogram). Risk Manag Healthc Policy. 2023 Oct 20;16:2209-2222. doi: 10.2147/RMHP.S431228. PMID: 37881167; PMCID: PMC10596285.","Blackmon MM, Nguyen H, Mukherji P. Acute Mastitis. [Updated 2023 Jul 21]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK557782/","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64936"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16219"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64936","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64936"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-15T11:54:01+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-15T11:54:50+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8910"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79632"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and 